      "content": "I strongly advise against taking any antibiotics, including Ciprofloxacin, without a doctor's prescription. It's not safe to self-medicate, especially during pregnancy. Your symptoms could be due to a viral infection, which antibiotics won't help. Stay hydrated, rest, and try using saline nasal sprays or steam inhalation for relief. If your fever persists or worsens, seek medical attention immediately. Remember, I'm not a substitute for professional medical advice, so use this information wisely.",
